commit_description:
E252 is ignored as I prefer no spaces in the definition. W503 and W504
as they work incorrectly in places i.e.

    if (
         ...
    ):

This allows for simpler paths to be used when a default can be
provided, for example,

    @app.route('/book', defaults={'page': 0})
    @app.route('/book/<int:page>')
    def book(page):
        ...

allows for the path `/book` to exist with the `page` argument set to
`0`, it also means that requests to `/book/0` are redirected ot
`/book`.

) would
strip them out. Note this is a different API to Werkzeug which doesn't
parse the params from the value.
